#: src/components/tile.tsx:96
msgid "Wednesday"
msgstr "Trečiadienis"

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/total-solar-eclipse.tsx:58
msgid "What it feels like"
msgstr "Ką tai primena"

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/quadrantids.tsx:83
msgid "When conditions are favourable, they produce sharp, fast-moving meteors in high numbers."
msgstr "Kai sąlygos palankios, jie sukuria daug aštrių, greitai judančių meteorų."

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/leonids.tsx:116
msgid "When this occurs, meteor rates can rise dramatically for a short period of time."
msgstr "Kai taip nutinka, meteorų skaičius trumpam gali smarkiai išaugti."

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/geminids.tsx:115
msgid "Whether your night air is warm or cool, a comfortable place to sit or lie back makes the experience far more enjoyable."
msgstr "Nesvarbu, ar nakties oras šiltas, ar vėsus, patogi vieta atsisėsti ar atsigulti paverčia patirtį kur kas malonesne."

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/total-lunar-eclipse.tsx:60
msgid "While eclipses were once viewed as omens, today they are widely appreciated as shared moments of skywatching and wonder."
msgstr "Nors užtemimai kadaise buvo laikomi ženklais, šiandien jie plačiai vertinami kaip bendri dangaus stebėjimo ir nuostabos momentai."

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/leonids.tsx:107
msgid "Why it can storm"
msgstr "Kodėl gali kilti audra"

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/total-lunar-eclipse.tsx:67
msgid "Why it turns red"
msgstr "Kodėl jis parausta"

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/quadrantids.tsx:106
msgid "Why the peak is brief"
msgstr "Kodėl pikas trumpas"

#: src/components/tile.tsx:251
msgid "Winter Solstice"
msgstr "Žiemos saulėgrįža"

#: src/hooks/seasonal-events/hanukkah.tsx:112
msgid "With each night, a new flame appears, forming a quiet ladder of light against the dark."
msgstr "Su kiekviena naktimi atsiranda nauja liepsna, sudarydama tylų šviesos laiptelį prieš tamsą."

#: src/components/review-prompt.tsx:40
